reviewText: Awsome it has inspired me

I will be brief, as the stories are familiar. These stories have been seemingly "Done to death" over the years. With knowing that, I believe you will be surprisingly pleased with these versions. I found many of the musical numbers very entertaining andthe animation is not bad. What made me take the time to write this 5 star review is the way the writers spin each tried-&-true story in a manner that kept me entertained and somewhat guessing how it would end. To accomplish THAT with this material deserves 5 stars. That and the way they handled the very unfortunate Romanov family. Kudos to the entire creative team. Well done, with many thanks!

My 3 and 4 year old daughters love the three stories in this series: Snow White, Anastasia and Mulan. Each of them takes great poetic license from the original story lines that I grew up with, but they are well narrated and the graphics are pleasing. I have watched all three with my girls to make sure they are appropriate. They definitely are. I REALLY enjoyed watching Snow White because the "Mirror, Mirror on the Wall" is a real character and the famous voice impersonations are excellent. They are good enough that I thought maybe Rich Little had been employed to do them. However, there are no credits given for impersonated voices, so I have no idea who does them. That's a shame - the person deserves credit!

The characters look a bit strange, and it is, so far, the worst version of Anastasia I have ever seen.  As I haven't seen the Mulan or Snow White version,  I can't really judge them, but for the Anastasia one, the songs are strange and the characters are weird.  I feel like it doesn't really have that much of a purpose, and doesn't have any strong themes and valuable lessons.  It's okay though,  I guess.

Mulan is a bug, Snow White is a mix of Goldilocks, a tiny bit of the story as you know it, and Wizard of Oz. The characters are obnoxious, songs are annoying, animation is weak, and comedy is pathetic. It must be student animators, because No one could've made money on this. I'm all for an interesting retelling of a classic story (like Wicked or Maleficent) but these were so mixed up and twisted, that it was just a train wreck.
It amuses ages 6 and under, but do yourself a favor and don't watch it with them.
